JustYourKicks Automation Framework using Playwright + JavaScript
Project Overview

This project is an End-to-End Automation Testing Framework developed for the JustYourKicks website using Playwright and JavaScript. The framework automates major user workflows such as product search, filtering, cart management, checkout flow, API validation, session persistence, and reporting. The framework follows the Page Object Model (POM) architecture to ensure better maintainability, reusability, and scalability.

Website Used

Website: justyourkicks.in

=> Technologies Used

• Playwright
• JavaScript
• Node.js
• Visual Studio Code
• HTML Reports
• Allure Report
• GitHub Actions
• Page Object Model (POM)
• API Testing
• Cross Browser Testing


=> Services Covered in Project

1. Authentication & User Account Service
2. Product Catalog & Brand Listing Service
3. Search, Categories & Filter Service
4. Product Details Page (PDP) Service
5. Cart Management Service
6. Wishlist Service
7. Checkout & Shipping Service
8. Order Placement & Payment Flow Service
9. User Profile & Session Persistence Service
10. Internal API Testing Service


=> Main Features

• 100+ Automated Test Cases
• Cross Browser Execution
• Screenshot Capture on Failure
• Video Recording of Test Execution
• Trace Viewer for Debugging
• Session Persistence Testing
• API Automation Testing
• HTML Reporting
• Allure Reporting
• Reusable Page Object Model (POM)
• CI/CD Integration using GitHub Actions


=> Project Objectives

The main objective of this project is to automate critical workflows of the JustYourKicks platform and improve testing efficiency.
The framework validates core functionalities, UI behavior, APIs, persistence, browser compatibility, and end-to-end user journeys while significantly reducing manual testing effort.


=> Expected Outputs

• HTML Report Generation
• Allure Report Dashboard
• Screenshots on Failed Tests
• Video Recording of Test Execution
• Trace Files for Debugging
• Cross Browser Execution Results
• API Validation Reports


=> Conclusion

This project demonstrates the development of a complete Automation Testing Framework using Playwright with JavaScript for the JustYourKicks platform.
It covers key testing areas including UI Automation, API Testing, Session Persistence, Reporting, Cross-Browser Testing, and CI/CD Integration.
The framework helps validate critical user workflows, improve test reliability, reduce manual effort, and ensure application quality through scalable and maintainable automation practices.